    <title>Egg Curry Recipe</title>
	<link href="~/css/eggurry.css" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

   

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🍛 Egg Curry</h1>
     
        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>4 Boiled Eggs</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Oil</li>
            <li>1 Onion (Finely Chopped)</li>
            <li>2 Tomatoes (Pureed)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>1 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Coconut Milk (Optional)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Coriander Leaves for Garnish</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Heat oil in a pan and add cumin seeds.</li>
            <li>Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and cook for a minute.</li>
            <li>Mix in tomato puree, turmeric, chili powder, and salt.</li>
            <li>Cook the mixture until the oil separates.</li>
            <li>Pour in coconut milk (optional) and bring to a simmer.</li>
            <li>Make small cuts on the boiled eggs and add them to the curry.</li>
            <li>Cook for 5 minutes and sprinkle garam masala.</li>
            <li>Garnish with coriander leaves and serve hot with rice or roti.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
